A Submodel defines a specific aspect of the asset represented by the AAS. A submodel is used to structure the digital representation and technical functionality of an Administration Shell into distinguishable parts. Each submodel refers to a well-defined domain or subject matter. Submodels can become standardized and thus become submodels types. Submodels can have different life-cycles.

A data element is a submodel element that is not further composed out of other submodel elements. A data element is a submodel element that has a value. The type of value differs for different subtypes of data elements.
A property is a data element that has a single value.
A submodel element collection is a set or list of submodel elements.
A submodel element collection is a set or list of submodel elements.
A File is a data element that represents an address to a file. The value is an URI that can represent an absolute or relative path.
A BLOB is a data element that represents a file that is contained with its source code in the value attribute.
A reference element is a data element that defines a logical reference to another element within the same or another AAS or a reference to an external object or entity.
A relationship element is used to define a relationship between two referable elements.
An operation variable is a submodel element that is used as input or output variable of an operation.
An operation is a submodel element with input and output variables.

A dictionary contains elements that can be reused. The concept dictionary contains concept descriptions. Typically a concept description dictionary of an AAS contains only concept descriptions of elements used within submodels of the AAS
A view is a collection of referable elements w.r.t. to a specific viewpoint of one or more stakeholders.

An Asset describes meta data of an asset that is represented by an AAS. The asset may either represent an asset type or an asset instance. The asset has a globally unique identifier plus – if needed – additional domain specific(proprietary) identifiers.

Ein Sensor ist bündig einbaubar, wenn beliebiger dämpfender Werkstoff um die aktive Fläche angebracht werden kann, ohne die kennzeichnenden Merkmale zu beeinflussen. Ein Sensor ist nicht bündig einbaubar, wenn eine bestimmte Freizone um seine aktive Fläche notwendig ist. Quasibündig gilt für Sensoren, die in ihrer Bauart einem bündigen Sensor entsprechen (also nicht die typische Kunststoffkappe des Freizonensensors haben) jedoch Freizonen-Schaltabstände aufweisen. Diese Sensoren sind meist nicht 100% bündig oder gar überbündig einbaubar, sondern brauchen eine kleine Freizone (Überstand)

a sensor can be installed flush if any restraining work substance/ material can be placed around the active surface without affecting its distinguishing characteriztics. A sensor cannot be installed flush if a certain free or open zone is required around its active surface. A sensor can be installed quasi-flush if its construction type allows for flush installation (and thus does not have the typical plastic cap of open zone sensors) but still have open zone switching states. these sensors are mostly not 100% flush or even over-flush installable, but need a small free or open zone (projecting length)
